> I feel a bit silly asking for help since I have been practicing our craft for almost two years now, but I refuse to be categorized with the weak and foolish rogues or assassins who think they know everything and do not believe there any new tricks to learn.<br>
<br>
What I am leading into is the ability to backstab an opponent, or a mob, while standing in front of them.  I have heard about this ability, and I have tried it many times while practicing on weak prey, but I had come to the conclusion that it was all just a rumor.  But then today, I overheard a rogue mention how they are able to do this very same feat.<br>
<br>
Would any of you who are able to do this be willing to share your secrets with the rest of us, or possibly point us in the right direction?  I used to be quite active in the Safehouse, but due to RL issues, I am unable to frequent here as much as I would like.  Any and all help is much appreciated by myself and the other thieves, assassins, cut-throats, highway men, and bandits of Norrath.<br>
<br>
/bow<br>
<br>
<br>
Larlana Lavode<br>
Mistress of Assassins<br>
The Wraithguard<br>
Tallon Zek  <br>
